    {"repo": "chromium/chromium", "path": "content/common/renderer.mojom", "symbol": "Renderer"}
  ],
  "text": "Chromium's multi-process architecture is defined across five key files:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h, line 195): This class represents the browser-side of the browser<-->renderer communication channel. It implements RenderProcessHost and serves as the browser process's representation of a renderer process. There is one RenderProcessHostImpl per renderer process.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h, line 106): This class implements the main browser loop stages and manages core browser resources. It owns the main message loop, thread pool, audio manager, media stream manager, and other essential browser components. The singleton instance is accessed via BrowserMainLoop::GetInstance().\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h, line 126): This class represents the main thread of a renderer process where blink::WebView instances live. It extends ChildThreadImpl and implements the mojom::Renderer interface. It handles routing of legacy IPC messages to RenderFrameImpl instances via routing IDs.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h, line 212): This class is responsible for spawning child processes asynchronously. It avoids blocking the calling thread by launching processes in the background and notifying clients via the Client interface when the process is ready or fails to launch.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** (content/common/renderer.mojom, line 49): This is the primary Channel-associated Mojo interface implemented by renderer processes. It defines the protocol for browser-to-renderer control messages that must retain FIFO ordering with legacy IPC messages."
}

